**Bug 5 (Confidence: 80)** — `RocketHUD.handleKey` at line 44-48 calls `e.preventDefault()` on ALL keydown events during `approaching`/`flash` states, with no ability to abort a docking sequence for 1.7 seconds. While browsers protect most of their own shortcuts, this blanket prevention is broader than necessary and provides no escape hatch for an accidentally triggered docking sequence.

File: `C:/Users/johnm/iskrib_v3/client/src/components/Universe/components/RocketHUD.jsx`, lines 44-48

Fix: Only call `e.preventDefault()` for the keys you actually handle (`Enter`, `Space`, `Escape`), or allow `Escape` to abort even during `approaching` by routing it to `abortDocking` (which currently only acts on `magnet` state — `approaching` is intentionally non-interruptible per the comment at line 648-649, so this is a design decision to revisit).
